<HEADLINE>
FT  08 SEP 94 / World Trade News: Lucas Aerospace in joint venture with
Chinese - Aviation industry contracts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD GRAY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Lucas Aerospace, the UK engineering company, is to form a joint venture with
the China National Aero-technology Import and Export Company, writes Bernard
Gray.
The joint venture will be shared equally and will have alternating chairmen,
but Lucas will have management control of the manufacturing plant near
Shanghai.
Initially, the joint venture will provide a digital engine control system
for the Chinese K-8 basic jet trainer. It will also be the preferred
supplier in future engine control, flight control and power generation
equipment. The venture could have a turnover in excess of Dollars 100m
within 10 years.
</TEXT>
