</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
President Francois Mitterrand has endorsed Mr Jacques Delors, outgoing
president of the European Commission, as the left-wing politician best
placed to run in France's presidential election next year. Asked who would
be the most competent candidate, the Socialist head of state said in an
interview published today by the newspaper Le Figaro: 'On the left, Jacques
