FT  08 SEP 94 / World News in Brief: Benetton team made 'honest mistake'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Flavio Briatore, managing director of Benetton Formula, arrived at the
International Automobile Federation in Paris to hear that his Formula One
motor racing team had escaped punishment for tampering with refuelling
equipment. The federation ruled that Benetton had made an 'honest mistake'
in removing a filter which led to a flash fire at July's German grand prix
in Hockenheim.
