FT  07 SEP 94 / Observer: Book squirm
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A revolution is about to erupt in that normally placid market, dictionary
publishing. Chambers is publishing an Encyclopedic (sic) English Dictionary
combining both lexical and encyclopaedic information and definitions. So
'bonzer' (Australian slang meaning good) will nestle close to
'Bosnia-Herzegovina' (Serbo-Croat for oh what an awful mess).
It must surely rank as one of the fastest-to-go-out-of-date publications in
history. How long will 'scuzzy' (US slang for filthy) or 'humungous'
(colloquial for enormous) last? But check out the entry for Macedonia. All
it says on 'economy' is 'market gardening'.
