FT  07 SEP 94 / Shop staff told to accept pay cuts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Northern Ireland Electricity has called on staff in its Shop Electric
high-street showrooms to accept new employment terms, including pay cuts
averaging 6.1 per cent - up to 14 per cent for some - or face the loss of
400 jobs.
To cushion the impact of the pay cuts, NIE Retail has offered full-time
staff Pounds 8,750 in compensation and a phasing-in of the reduction for
those worst hit.
