FT  07 SEP 94 / World News in Brief: Pope postpones visit to Sarajevo
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pope John Paul postponed a visit to the Bosnian capital Sarajevo tomorrow
after failing to receive security guarantees. Bosnian Serbs, whose forces
surround Sarajevo, refused to provide assurances that Sarajevans who turned
out to greet the Pope would be safe. They said Moslems would stage an
incident and then blame the Serbs. Two United Nations aircraft were hit by
small arms fire at the city's airport, where the papal aircraft would have
landed.
