businesses rose from Pounds 62.8m to Pounds 64.3m.
The company's security and building sectors both showed improvements - at
Pounds 1m (Pounds 0.9m) and Pounds 1.8m (Pounds 1.7m) respectively - while
the industrial side, although Pounds 0.5m lower than last time at Pounds
0.6m, showed a recovery on last year's difficult second half.
The lower interest charge reflected both reduced borrowings and a fall in
French interest rates. At June 30, borrowings including leasing, had reduced
by 20 per cent or Pounds 4m compared to mid-1993.
Earnings per share were 2.71p (2.59p) and the interim dividend has been
lifted from 1.25p to 1.35p.
</TEXT>
